text.tspan: Vaping is the act of inhaling and exhaling the aerosol often referred to as
vapor produced by an e-cigarette or a similar device. It is called vaping
because e-cigarettes do not produce tobacco smoke but an aerosol
often mistaken for wtaer vapour that actually contains fine particles.
Many of these particles contain varying amounts of toxic chemicals,
which have been linked to heart and respiratory diseases and cancer.
